        "Raise to 8th: $(\\sqrt{2})^8 (\\cos 2\\pi + i\\sin 2\\pi) = 16 \\cdot 1 = 16$."
      ],
      "explanation": "$|1+i|^8 = (\\sqrt{2})^8 = 16$. Argument $\\times 8 = 2\\pi$, cos = 1, sin = 0. So $16$.",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "**Polar form:** $1 + i = \\sqrt{2}\\,e^{i\\pi/4}$."
        },
        {
          "text": "**Apply De Moivre:**"
        },
        {
          "math": "(1 + i)^8 = (\\sqrt{2})^8 \\cdot e^{i \\cdot 8\\pi/4} = 16 \\cdot e^{i \\cdot 2\\pi}"
        },
        {
          "math": "= 16(\\cos 2\\pi + i\\sin 2\\pi) = 16 \\cdot 1 = 16"
        }
      ],
      "difficulty": "hard"
